Government initiatives to control parasitic infections, including schistosomiasis, are also contributing to the growth of the treatment market. Governments in various regions are implementing programs and policies to address the burden of schistosomiasis and other neglected tropical diseases. These initiatives often involve collaborations with healthcare providers, pharmaceutical companies, and other stakeholders to ensure effective treatment and management of the disease. Such efforts are expected to drive the adoption of schistosomiasis treatment options, thereby propelling market growth.

